  "text": "Cross-org WebIDL to DOM Binding Discovery - Fetch API Analysis\n\nThis analysis identifies the WebIDL interface definitions for the Fetch API in Firefox and their corresponding C++ binding implementations.\n\nFetch API Interface Mappings:\n\n1. Request Interface:\n   - WebIDL Definition: dom/webidl/Request.webidl\n   - C++ Header: dom/fetch/Request.h\n   - C++ Implementation: dom/fetch/Request.cpp\n   - Description: Defines the Request interface for the Fetch API (https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#request-class). The C++ implementation provides the Request constructor and methods for controlling request parameters including method, URL, headers, credentials, cache policy, and abort signal handling.\n\n2. Response Interface:\n   - WebIDL Definition: dom/webidl/Response.webidl\n   - C++ Header: dom/fetch/Response.h\n   - C++ Implementation: dom/fetch/Response.cpp\n   - Description: Defines the Response interface for the Fetch API (https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#response-class). Includes response status, headers, body handling, and static factory methods for creating error and redirect responses.\n\n3. Headers Interface:\n   - WebIDL Definition: dom/webidl/Headers.webidl\n   - C++ Header: dom/fetch/Headers.h\n   - C++ Implementation: dom/fetch/Headers.cpp\n   - Description: Defines the Headers interface for managing HTTP header collections (http://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#headers-class). Provides methods for appending, deleting, getting, setting headers, and iteration support.\n\n4. FetchEvent Interface:\n   - WebIDL Definition: dom/webidl/FetchEvent.webidl\n   - C++ Header: dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.h\n   - C++ Implementation: dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.cpp\n   - Description: Defines the FetchEvent interface for Service Worker fetch event handling (http://slightlyoff.github.io/ServiceWorker/spec/service_worker/index.html). The FetchEvent class extends ExtendableEvent and provides access to the intercepted request, preload response promise, client IDs, and the respondWith() method for providing custom responses.\n\nAdditional Context:\n- The dom/webidl/Fetch.webidl file defines the Body mixin and other core Fetch API types (BodyInit, FetchReadableStreamReadData) that are used across Request and Response interfaces.\n- All WebIDL files are located in the mozilla-firefox/firefox repository under dom/webidl/.\n- Request, Response, and Headers implementations are in dom/fetch/ directory.\n- FetchEvent implementation is in dom/serviceworkers/ directory because it is Service Worker specific.\n- The implementations use WebIDL bindings generated from these IDL files, providing JavaScript-accessible DOM APIs."
}

